The paper discusses the use of Deep Q-Networks (DQN) for optimizing traffic light control policies in Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITSs). This involves the application of reinforcement learning techniques to a complex real-world problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with control systems and optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as likely candidates. Finally, the paper also involves the use of robotics and automation, which could place it in the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
